This paper primarily focuses on improving software security by introducing a new memory allocator. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the allocator, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for memory allocation, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
